    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_D7ED3570-18B0-0135-B022-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Depending on how your Canvas account was created, you may be able to make changes to your name, <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-select-personal-pronouns-in-my-user-account-as-a/ta-p/456" target="_blank">pronouns</a>, default email, <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-change-the-language-preference-in-my-user-account-as-a/ta-p/436" target="_blank">language</a>, <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-set-a-time-zone-in-my-user-account-as-a-student/ta-p/414" target="_blank">time zone</a>, and <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-change-my-login-password-as-a-student/ta-p/425" target="_blank">password</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>Setting a chosen language will override any default language settings across your institution; however, any language set in a course will override your user language.</li>
<li>Your institution may take care of updating or changing your password by using the password associated with your login credentials for Canvas.</li>
<li>Users associated with a SIS ID cannot delete their own account.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> Some settings may not be available to you. If you are not able to edit your user settings, you will need to contact your institution to change this information.</p>
  </div>
</div>

    <div class="html-embed">
  <iframe width="700px" height="400px" src="https://embed.app.guidde.com/playbooks/msZwZR5Uv41LDrteDTNm8z" title="How do I change the settings in my user account as a student?" frameborder="0" referrerpolicy="unsafe-url" allowfullscreen="true" allow="clipboard-write" sandbox="allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-scripts allow-forms allow-same-origin allow-presentation"></iframe>
<p style="display: none">

00:00: How do I change the settings in my user account as a student?

00:04: In Global Navigation, click the Account link.

00:08: Then click the Settings link.

00:11: Click the Edit Settings button.

00:14: If enabled, edit the appropriate settings:

00:17: Full Name is used for the Gradebook and Grades pages, Chat, People, and SIS imports.

00:24: Display Name is how other users will see your name in Announcements, Conferences, Conversations, and Discussions.

00:32: Sortable Name defaults to your last name, first name and appears in sorted lists so admins can search for it.

00:39: Pronouns display after your name in various areas throughout Canvas.

00:44: Default Email can be set when you have multiple Notification email addresses associated with your account.

00:51: Language can be set to your native language and is the language you want to use in Canvas (does not apply if an instructor sets a specific language for a course).

01:00: Time Zone can be set to where you are located and displays assignments in your local time.

01:06: Password is the combination of characters you choose to use to log in to your Canvas account.

01:12: Click the Update Settings button.

01:15: This guide covers how to change the settings in a user account as a student.

</p>
</div>


      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_user_settings" data-step-uuid="70616283-c323-4a72-ae29-8a3cf90e6823">
    <h2 id="open_user_settings" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open User Settings</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/008/304/932/original/087a0df3-d31a-4727-ba4d-768c98229a9e.png" srcset="" alt="Open User Settings" height="617" width="457">
